			<div id="review-33671" class="review-row media row">
				<div class="col-xs-2">

					<div class="rev-author-img">
													<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-user"></span>
							
					</div>

					<small class="container rev-author-meta mt10">
																					AGMECO Faucets Pvt. Ltd.																								</small>
				</div>

				<div class="col-xs-10 media-body">
					<div class="rev-wrap arrow_box">
						<!-- REVIEW CONTENT -->
							<h4 class="rev-heading"><a href="http://www.besthospitaladvisor.com/medical-providers/medanta-the-medicity/reviews/33671#rev">"Recently we have experienced..."</a></h4>
							<div class="rev-rating rating-input">
								<i class='glyphicon glyphicon-star'></i><i class='glyphicon glyphicon-star-empty'></i><i class='glyphicon glyphicon-star-empty'></i><i class='glyphicon glyphicon-star-empty'></i><i class='glyphicon glyphicon-star-empty'></i> <small class="rev-date">Reviewed 4 weeks ago</small>
                                                                    <img style="margin-left:15px;" src="/images/powered-by-google.png">
                                                            </div>
							<p class="rev-body">
								Recently we have experienced with our own patient and have seen few other patients and came to a conclusion that the Hospital is not sterilized well. There is every chances of a patient or attendant catching<span class="show-more"><span class="more-link">... <a href="#">more</a></span><span class="more-text hidden"> infection and that too deadly sort of that they can lose their life too, as it happened with our patient. He was admitted for pre-clearance of liver transplantation and very unfortunately expired due to a deadly chest infection caught within the hospital during his stay, which could never be cured or handled properly by doctors in the liver transplantation unit / ICU. He was admitted under famous Dr. A.S. Soin. Even the donor, who was patient's attendant during the stay, also caught the chest infection but luckily he was young, healthy and refrained from visiting hospital further and was saved. Similiarly, an elderly patient admitted for heart surgery caught a stomach infection and is now in ICU. One neighbouring patient to our patient, was also suffering from infection caught during his stay in hospital. Even ICU seems to be worse in case of infection. Because, infection gets worsened after admission into ICU. We have a strong doubt that it is well known to doctors in ICU but they refrain from getting ICU sterilized properly by vacating the ICU for few days, because of lose of hefty amounts they earn from ICU. If some Ministry level person come acrosee this review, I would humbly request him to get the hospital audited properly for sterilization because CMD of this hospital is a powerful man and we small common people of India can't raise a voice against him or his hospital. I would also request to take proper punitive action against this hospital to save life of others because this money mongering hospital seem to be playing with life of patients just not to let its revenue fall in any case.<br />
<br />
Dear reader this is a serious factual observation so please don't discard it in any case, while getting your patient admitted here.<br />
<br />
We agree with one attendant Mr. Muhammad Fiaz, whose review has been posted herein below about one year ago. Exactly in similar way and exactly same negligence of Dr. A. S. SOIN, took place with our patient and he succumbed to this negligency of hospital. I wrote email and sent sms to Dr. A. S. Soin but failed to get response or update of the situation, when our patient was in critical state.</span></span>							</p>

