							<p class="rev-body">
								This got to be one of the worst hospitals around the area, we took our dad less than 2 years ago for a heart surgery, there was a senior sardar doctor who operated on him, i live in US so i don't recall<span class="show-more"><span class="more-link">... <a href="#">more</a></span><span class="more-text hidden"> his name, this was a major bypass surgery per them and everything went well until a month passed and he had the same chest pain again and they refused to admit, we talked and talked and somehow through our connections got the bed there, they found major blockages again in the same arteries, can you believe this, they told us that they were not sure how they missed it, they put the stents in, yesterday my dad again had the same problem, and we took him to another hospital, and they still found the same arteries blocked and ended up doing 3 stents again, just unbelievable how irresponsible, careless Medanta folks are, this last episode has literally pushed me to write this review so that anyone else living in that area could see the picture, the rudeness of these senior doctors in India was still bearable if they could do the job right, but apparently they cant even do that correctly, shame on the staff and this place.</span></span>							</p>

